<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>It is possible to return an object in service using Zend Rest Server.
But in my application it results in an DOMException, because one of the protected properties couldn't be converted to a XML element.</p>

<p>In Zend_Rest_Server::_structValue() $struct is always casted to an array like this:
$struct = (array) $struct;</p>

<p>This shouldn't be necessary, because it is always possible to iterate objects with foreach. 
Especially when all returned objects implementing IteratorAggregate</p>

<p>I use the same service class with Zend_Amf_Server which iterate objects without any problems.</p>

